s-boracay-located-in-aklan.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/where-is-boracay-located-in-aklan.jpg 1290w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/where-is-boracay-located-in-aklan-300x199.jpg 300w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/where-is-boracay-located-in-aklan-1024x678.jpg 1024w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/where-is-boracay-located-in-aklan-768x508.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1290px) 100vw, 1290px\" />													\n			<h3>Boracay</h3><p>Boracay is a small island in the central Philippines. It\'s known for its resorts and beaches. Along the west coast, White Beach is backed by palm trees, bars and restaurants. On the east coast, strong winds make Bulabog Beach a hub for water sports. Nearby, the observation deck on Mount Luho offers panoramic views over the island. Offshore, coral reefs and shipwrecks are home to diverse marine life.</p>		\n													<img width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" src=\"http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/8-siargao-island-banner-2022.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/8-siargao-island-banner-2022.jpg 1500w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/8-siargao-island-banner-2022-300x180.jpg 300w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/8-siargao-island-banner-2022-1024x614.jpg 1024w, http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/8-siargao-island-banner-2022-768x461.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" />													\n			<h3>Siargo Island</h3><p>Siargao is a tear-drop shaped island in the Philippine Sea situated 196 kilometers southeast of Tacloban. It has a land area of approximately 437 square kilometres. The east coast is relatively straight with one deep inlet, Port Pilar.</p>		\n													<img src=\"http://localhost/blog-post/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/quotes.svg\" alt=\"\" />													\n			<h4>Original and with 